<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: BEVERLY HILLS; 
GORBACHEV ASKS WORLDWIDE ENVIRONMENTAL 'PERESTROIKA' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ex-Soviet President Mikhail Gorbachev, who heads an international ecological 
crusade, called for an international environmental "perestroika" on the second 
day of his two-day mission in the Los Angeles area. 
</P>
<P>
 "The role of the U.S. in the post-Cold War could be more important than its 
role was in the past," the former head of the now-defunct Soviet Union said 
Tuesday at a Town Hall luncheon in Beverly Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 "This country has the potential to be a leader in a new world order," he said 
through an interpreter. "The most important expression of that would be in the 
environment." 
</P>
<P>
 Gorbachev founded Green Cross International in 1993, two years after he was 
deposed as Soviet leader. Global Green U.S.A., founded last year, will be an 
affiliate of the international group, Gorbachev said. 
</P>
<P>
 The American group will join Gorbachev in his campaign to get people in all 
countries to stop mistreating the earth, fix man-made disasters and reform 
ecological law, he said.  
</P>
<P>
 Gorbachev, flanked by his wife, Raisa, said that during the Cold War, the 
world was divided and "nobody had time for the environment." Times have 
changed, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
