<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; BOY WOUNDED IN HEAD IN POOL HALL SHOOTING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 14-year-old boy remained hospitalized Tuesday after being wounded by gunfire 
in a Garden Grove pool hall, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police, who withheld the boy's name, said he was hit at least once in the head 
Monday night when a man opened fire with a small-caliber handgun inside the 
Paris Billiard Cafe in the 10000 block of Garden Grove Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 The boy was listed in stable condition at UCI Medical Center in Orange, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Lt. John Woods said four men in a van pulled up in front of the billiards hall 
about 8:15 p.m. Monday. Two men ran inside and one of them fired the shots with 
a semiautomatic weapon, Woods said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police were investigating the incident as gang-related, Woods said. He said 
police believe the boy was not the intended target of the attack, but 
investigators had not determined who was. 
