<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: TOURISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Knott's Hears Overture From Ozarks: A landowner in Branson, Mo., says he has 
talked to Knott's Berry Farm representatives about building an amusement park 
on 340 acres he owns in this Ozarks music mecca."I have talked to them, as I 
have to other interested parties, but there's nothing official yet," said 
Marvin Motley. Until now, the only Knott's venture outside Buena Park has been 
a licensing agreement that allowed the creation of Knott's Camp Snoopy at the 
huge Mall of America in Minneapolis. Knott's Berry Farm spokesman Bob Ochsner 
said Tuesday that he couldn't confirm any expansion plans. 
</P>
