Century Industries announced the signing of definitive agreements under which 
AIG will invest an initial $216 million -- and possibly up to $432 million -- 
in 20th Century and the two insurers will embark on joint ventures to sell auto 
insurance nationally. New York-based AIG will pay $200 million for a new issue 
