<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALSA TO PLAY 19 EXHIBITIONS AGAINST MEXICAN FIRST DIVISION TEAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Salsa announced Tuesday a 19-match series against soccer teams from the 
Mexican First Division, which will run through April, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 The series begins at 7:30 p.m. Saturday, Oct. 29, when the Salsa plays host to 
Chivas of Guadalajara in Weingart Stadium at East Los Angeles College. 
</P>
<P>
 Most games will be played at Weingart with two -- Nov. 30 against Tampico and 
Jan. 28 against Morella -- scheduled for Titan Stadium in Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The Salsa has been invited to participate in the First Division, but that plan 
remains on hold. This series will give the team a chance to compete against 
"some of the best players on the continent," according to Coach Rick Davis. 
</P>
<P>
 U.S. World Cup veteran Hugo Perez and Paulinho, named the American 
Professional Soccer League's most valuable player for the second consecutive 
year, will lead the Salsa. 
</P>
<P>
 Individual match tickets are $20 for adults and $10 for children under 14. 
Season tickets for all 19 games are available before Oct. 29 for $169.  
</P>
<P>
 The series' dates and opponents (subject to change; unless noted, site is 
Weingart Stadium, game time 7:30 p.m.; * -- to be confirmed): 
</P>
<P>
 OCT. 29 -- Chivas. NOV. 5 -- Puebla; 12 -- Veracruz; 23 -- Atlas, 8 p.m.; 30 
-- Tampico, 8 p.m., Titan Stadium. DEC. 3 -- Necaxa*; 10 -- Toluca; 17 -- 
Monterrey; 22 -- Leon, 8 p.m. JAN. 7 -- UAG; 14 -- Santos; 21 -- Cruz Azul*; 28 
-- Morelia, Titan Stadium. FEB. 4 -- Atlante; 11 -- Correcaminos; 18 -- 
Tigres*; 25 -- Toros Neza*. March 25 -- America*. April 1 -- Pumas. 
