<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: STUDIO CITY; GALLERY SEEKS KIDS' CREEPY CREATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Children and teen-agers around the San Fernando Valley will attempt to capture 
the spirits of Halloween on canvas, paper or any other medium they choose for a 
contest sponsored by ACHIEVEMENT through ART. 
</P>
<P>
 The organization works toward funding college scholarships for local art 
students.Coordinated by Studio City's DECOR ART Gallery, the founding agency of 
ACHIEVEMENT through ART, the contest, called "Creative Halloween Art Contest 
for Students," will be judged by professionals from the entertainment industry. 
Judges will include a scenic design artist from the "Star Trek: Deep Space 
Nine" art department and directors of a student internship program at Film 
Roman, a North Hollywood-based production company for children's television 
programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Entries will be divided into three categories: grades one through six, seven 
through nine, and 10 through 12. Winners from each category will receive cash 
prizes and gifts for their efforts, with $75 for first-place winners, $50 for 
second place and $25 for third.  
</P>
<P>
 Winning entries will be framed by DECOR ART Gallery. 
</P>
<P>
 To enter, students must submit their work to the gallery at 12149 Ventura 
Blvd., Studio City. Entries must be received by Oct. 27. There is no entry fee. 
</P>
<P>
 Winners will be announced Oct. 30 at a free exhibition and party at the art 
gallery from 10:30 a.m. to 1:30 p.m.. 
</P>
<P>
 For entry specifications and additional information, call (818) 755-0755. 
ANTONIO OLIVO 
