<TEXT>
<P>
 Ever wonder why Laguna Niguel's city motto is "Sea Country," even though the 
South County community doesn't touch the ocean? 
</P>
<P>
 And why the Ritz-Carlton -- Laguna Niguel hotel is actually located within the 
city of Dana Point? 
</P>
<P>
 Back in the 1960s, realtors touted the Laguna Niguel planned community as "Sea 
Country" because the development stretched to the ocean south of Laguna Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 But in the 1980s, residents of Laguna Niguel's coastal section, known as 
Monarch Beach, voted to incorporate with Dana Point. So the Ritz-Carlton hotel 
became part of Dana Point in everything but name. And the city known as "Sea 
Country" became landlocked. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Retiring Supervisor Thomas F. Riley will be honored by the Mental Health Assn. 
of Orange County at noon at the Irvine Marriott hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 The association will inaugurate an annual community service award named in 
Riley's honor. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine psychiatry professor Dr. William Bunney will be the keynote speaker, 
discussing new research in schizophrenia. 
</P>
<P>
 Former association President Mary Evelyn Bryden will also be honored. 
