<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; USC; SAFETY KNIGHT PLAYED HIS BEST GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By EARL GUSTKEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Safety Sammy Knight approached star level in the Trojans' 27-20 victory at 
Stanford on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Coach John Robinson has compared sophomore Knight to former Trojan secondary 
greats Ronnie Lott and Dennis Thurman, but until Saturday he didn't always have 
his aggressive game under control. 
</P>
<P>
 But at Stanford, he had seven unassisted tackles and four assists. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tailback Shawn Walters' 234-yard game against Stanford was his second 
200-yarder this season. He ran for 207 against Baylor Sept. 24. 
</P>
<P>
 Walters, with 712 yards, has a chance to become the first Trojan to register a 
1,000-yard season since Mazio Royster in 1990 (1,168). 
</P>
<P>
 The NCAA season record for 200-yard games is eight, by USC's Marcus Allen, in 
1981.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The grand theft trial of receiver Keyshawn Johnson has been continued to 
Monday in Van Nuys Municipal Court because prosecutors cannot find their 
witness, defense attorney Michael C. Carney said. EARL GUSTKEY 
