<HEADLINE>
<P>
TV RATINGS; ROSEANNE'S TV BIO: FEW VIEWERS SEEM TO CARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LEE MARGULIES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 While her work remains appreciated, apparently there is a limit to how much 
the world wants to know about Roseanne. Viewers in nearly three times as many 
homes tuned in to watch the actress perform in her popular ABC sitcom last week 
than to see a TV movie on Fox about her seesaw life. 
</P>
<P>
 The film, "Roseanne: An Unauthorized Biography," ranked 91st among 94 
prime-time network programs on the ratings list released Tuesday by the A.C. 
Nielsen Co. 
</P>
<P>
 And while Fox had nine other shows among Nielsen's 15 lowest rated, it did 
have one bright spot in "Beverly Hills, 90210." Now in its fifth year,the drama 
was the most-watched program in its Wednesday time slot last week, beating 
comedies on ABC and CBS and "The Cosby Mysteries" on NBC. Among all programs, 
it ranked 29th nationally and 7th locally. 
</P>
<P>
 CBS, after winning the previous week, fell back to third, a tick behind NBC, 
while ABC recorded its third victory in the four-week-old season. NBC is the 
big surprise, showing the most ratings growth among any of the networks and 
boasting the two highest-rated newcomers, "ER" and "Madman of the People." 
Southland Ratings 
</P>
<P>
 Here are A. C. Nielsen's Top 10 prime-time programs in the Los Angeles area 
during the same week. Each rating point equals 50,064 households. 
04,33,09,06,06 Sta- Rat- Program tion ing 1. Seinfeld KNBC 21.5 2. Roseanne 
KABC 19.6 3. Home Improvement KABC 19.1 4. 60 Minutes KCBS 18.3 5. ER KNBC 17.1 
6. Grace Under Fire KABC 16.8 7. Beverly Hills, 90210 KTTV 16.2 8. Frasier KNBC 
16.1 9. Murder, She Wrote KCBS 16.0 10. Married . . . With Children KTTV 15.8 
