<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mayra Medina 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Valley, Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 Cross-country 
</P>
<P>
 Medina, from Laguna Hills High, appears to be in good shape as she starts the 
stretch run of her community college career. She placed third in a field of 118 
at the Mt.San Antonio Invitational Friday, with a time of 19 minutes five 
seconds on the demanding 5,000-meter course. Medina and her Irvine Valley 
teammates, defending State champions, will compete in the Moorpark Invitational 
(Oct. 29), the Orange Empire Conference championship (Nov. 5) and the State 
meet (Nov. 19). Soccer 
