<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Profile 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA101994-0230 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 090149 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
October 19, 1994, Wednesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Sports; Part C; Page 5; Column 1; Sports Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
133 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ATHLETES OF THE WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Jeff Clayton 
</P>
<P>
 Orange Coast, Sophomore 
</P>
<P>
 Football/Running back 
</P>
<P>
 Clayton, from Trabuco Hills High, spend his first year at Orange Coast as a 
redshirt. He spent his time being punished by the first-team defense in 
practice.But Clayton has since gotten his revenge on the opposition. Clayton 
had 115 yards in OCC's 28-21 loss Saturday to San Diego Mesa and became the 
all-time leading rusher in OCC history. Clayton has gained 1,983 yards in 16 
games. He also has rushed for 100 or more yards in 11 starts. Clayton rushed 
for 1,442 yards as a freshman. Football 
</P>
<P>
