<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: SPRINGMAN NAMED COACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bill Springman, a former assistant at Pepperdine University, has been hired as 
baseball coach at Oak Park High. Springman succeeds Mike Bolyog, who resigned 
in June after three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
 Oak Park also announced that Zoran Lomic will move from girls' to boys' soccer 
coach. Ted Eggleston, a former youth coach, will replace Lomic as girls' coach. 
Football 
</P>
<P>
 The condition of Peter Forlano of Notre Dame High is improving, but the player 
remains hospitalized after undergoing brain surgery last week, Forlano's mother 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Forlano, a starting senior tackle, was admitted to St. Joseph Medical Center 
in Burbank on Oct. 7 after experiencing dizziness, numbness of the right arm 
and blurred vision. 
</P>
<P>
 Doctors determined that Forlano was struck by a severe bacterial sinus 
infection, Alice Forlano said. But he has regained movement of his arm and his 
condition continues to improve. 
</P>
<P>
 Westlake High receiver Billy Miller said doctors prescribed a few days of rest 
for his sore left knee, but he expects to play in Friday's key Marmonte League 
game against Royal. Miller injured his knee last week against Newbury Park. 
Cross-Country 
</P>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks High boys' cross-country team has dropped from second to 
fifth in The Harrier magazine's national poll. Hart has moved from 23rd to 
13th. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks' girls' team is ranked 15th. 
</P>
