<TEXT>
<P>
 FCC Ordered to Reconsider Integrated Operation: The Federal Communications 
Commission must review the permission it gave regional Bell companies to offer 
electronic voice mail, other information services and telephone service under 
one roof, a federal appeals court ruled. The FCC has not yet shown why the 
public benefits of combined operations, which it has allowed for nearly a 
decade, outweigh the costs, said the 9th U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals.The 
court had reached the same conclusion in 1990 in response to an earlier FCC 
decision. The ruling should have no immediate effect on the so-called Baby 
Bells or their customers, because the companies are likely to seek another 
emergency FCC order allowing combined operations to continue, said a regional 
Bell source who asked not to be identified. 
